#load in the rhythmicity analysis results

syn_R <- read.csv("mmc proteins filtered H-syn RAIN.csv", stringsAsFactors = F)

total_R <- read.csv("mmc proteins filtered total RAIN.csv", stringsAsFactors = F)

#synprop_R <- read.csv("mmc proteins filtered H-prop RAIN.csv", stringsAsFactors = F)


#rhythmic based on RAIN
syn_rhy <- syn_R %>% filter(pVal<0.05)
total_rhy <- total_R %>% filter(pVal<0.05)

syntot_R <- merge(syn_R, total_R, by="Leading.razor.protein", suffixes=c(".syn", ".tot"))

write.csv(syntot_R, "mmc proteins synthesis and total RAIN.csv", row.names = F)

#divide into 4 sets based on "rhythmicity""

nonrhy <- syntot_R %>% filter(pVal.syn>0.05 & pVal.tot>0.05) #

#compare phase plots of these 

#function to plot
axis_colour = "grey85"
axis_text_size = 10

plottheme <- theme(axis.text.x = element_text(color = "black", size = axis_text_size, vjust = 0),
        axis.title.y = element_blank(), 
        axis.text.y = element_blank(),
        axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
        panel.grid = element_blank(),
        panel.border = element_blank(),
        plot.background = element_rect(fill="transparent"),
        panel.background = element_rect(fill = "transparent"),
        legend.box.background = element_blank(),
        legend.text = element_text(size = axis_text_size)
        )

phasepl <- function(data, ph, maxh, t) {
  ggplot(data, aes(x = ph)) + 
  geom_hline(yintercept = seq(0, maxh, by = maxh/5), colour = axis_colour, size = 0.2) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = seq(6, 24, 6), colour = axis_colour, size = 0.2) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth=6, aes(fill = ..count..)) +
  scale_x_continuous(name = t,
                     breaks = seq(6, 24, 6),
                     position = "top") +
  scale_fill_gradient("Count", low="blue", high="red") +
plottheme +
  coord_polar(theta = "x", start = (-45*pi)/180, direction = 1) # CHANGE THE ANGLE IN TO ALTER ROTATION - must be in radians, or just add to the formula
}



p1 <- phasepl(rhy_synonly, rhy_synonly$phase.syn, 300, "rhythmic in synthesis only")
p2 <- phasepl(rhy_totonly, rhy_totonly$phase.syn, 300, "rhythmic in total only")

pl <- grid.arrange(p1, p2)

#ggsave(plot=pl, "phases radial plots.pdf", height=6, width=3)


p3 <- phasepl(rhy_both, rhy_both$phase.syn, 300, "rhythmic in both,\n synthesis phase")
p4 <- phasepl(rhy_both, rhy_both$phase.tot, 300, "rhythmic in both,\n total phase")

pl <- grid.arrange(p1, p2, p3, p4, nrow=2)

#ggsave(plot=pl, "phases radial plots.pdf", height=6, width=6)


p_syn <- phasepl(syn_rhy, syn_rhy$phase, 500, "rhythmic in synthesis")
p_tot <- phasepl(total_rhy, total_rhy$phase, 500, "rhythmic in total")

pl <- grid.arrange(p_syn, p_tot, nrow=1)

ggsave(plot=pl, "phases radial plots 2.pdf", height=3, width=6)
